Business Brief -- Medusa Corp.:
   Company to Take a Charge
   Against Earnings for 1991
Medusa said the after-tax charge has two parts: First is
$13.7 million, or $1.28 a share, for a one-time "catch-up"
adjustment for years past, a charge that will be taken
against first-quarter 1991 earnings. Before the charge,
Medusa's first-quarter loss was $3.5 million, or 33 cents a
share. The second part of the charge is $1 million, or nine
cents a share, that will be applied against earnings for the
entire fiscal year. For the three quarters ended Sept.30,
Medusa earned $5.9 million, or 55 cents a share.